                            <comment id="13216765" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 26 Feb 2012 15:33:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4500&quot; title=&quot;Add a Tracer that uses JMX Notifications and provides full details of Camel Messages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-4500&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-4500&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a leak as well, in terms of ManagedTracer being kept around in a separate Map. We need to remove not needed tracer from that map as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13217085" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2012 07:12:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5046&quot; title=&quot;Memory leak when adding/removing a lot of routes with JMX enabled related to Tracer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-5046&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-5046&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to track the leak from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4500&quot; title=&quot;Add a Tracer that uses JMX Notifications and provides full details of Camel Messages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-4500&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-4500&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with ManagedTracer as it only affects 2.9 onwards.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
